title: Rumor: Avengers 4 Picks Up Five Years After Infinity War

summary: Infinity War Directors Cast Doubt On Resurrecting Certain MCU Characters
title: Infinity War Directors Cast Doubt On Resurrecting Certain MCU Characters
excerpt: Infinity War directors Joe & Anthony Russo hint they don't have to resurrect certain superheroes in its sequel thanks to the fluid MCU timeline.
description: Nah. I would bet money, GOTG3, Black Panther 2 and Spider-man: Homecoming 2 will all be set after Infinity War/Avengers 4. I mean, sure, they aren’t wrong in the point they are making and it’s not like they can say “yeah, they are all totally going to get resurrected.”

summary: do you think they're going to bring jane foster back to become the next thor? personally i wish they didn't... bring her back...
question: do you think they're going to bring jane foster back to become the next thor? personally i wish they didn't... bring her back...
answer:
I dont think they will make her the next thor, mcu is not the comics

BUT HOW could you not be excited about her potential return!! Like she was probably the only human who survives the Infinity Stone. I mean Im still confuse about the reality stone in Thor 2 why it picked Jane as a host, so if Marvel is actually gonna address that and not just brush off yet another female character, I AM ALL HERE FOR IT. 

And her return is not out of the blue, it makes sense. She is her own character, not just a ‘love interest’ to Thor (Also they broke up, so we can stop referring her to that!). She is an astrophysicist, she is an expertise in space and quantum physics, her knowledge is a great asset to the remaining Avengers when your fight is against a space titan who has all the infinity stones. You know for all its flaws Thor 2 had its heart in the right place, only because the execution was a bit messy it didn’t take away the fact that it was Jane, it was her knowledge and idea who played the key role in defeating the dark elf. 

So like why the marvel fans are only into all these physically badass female characters, but when a character like Jane, who is not here to fight with her physique but with her brain, who is not here to throw one liners but it’s here to help, and fans all immediately become so unwelcoming, deem her boring, unnecessary. Like, feminism is not just celebrating your Strong Kickass Female CharatcersTM, it is to celebrate and pay respect to ALL WOMEN. Because how many of us are actually spies, princess, goddess, in the military, fight villains every other night, kick asses take names every day? While it’s cool to have those physically strong female characters to look up to, to empower and inspire us, It is also really important to have relatable characters who have an every day job, who eats ice cream when she’s sad, yells at you when she’s mad, and in their rather ordinary life they are shown to have achieved extraordinary things. Can we all just appreciate female characters like that more, because they represent us.
